				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In my sound engine, the way I've been silencing the triangle channel is by making two very quick writes to $4015: $0B and then $0F. Basically, I quickly flip the Triangle's 'enabled' bit off and then back on. So far, this seems to work fine in emulators, but I haven't been able to test it on hardware or anything. It *seems* to work just fine in that it does silence the triangle channel, without actually turning it off, but is this behavior reliable at all?
<br />
<br />Moreover, would this technique work with the squares and the noise channel as well?</div>

