				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As I understand it, it turns off the length counter. To turn it back on, you need to write to $400b again.
<br />
<br />My sound engine uses one set of code for channels 1-4. Triangle is treated almost like the pulse channels: $4008 = $00 for off and $Bx for on, so I can treat it just like a 50% duty wave on the pulse channel, except smoother and an octave lower. Just remember that when you turn it back on, you need to rewrite the high byte of the period.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

